The paper discusses a method for solving Stackelberg games where the follower's utility function is unknown, using only revealed preference feedback. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.AI), as well as optimization (cs.DS) and decision making (cs.LG). The paper also discusses congestion games, which fall under the category of computer science and economics (cs.EC).
